faq:
  title: Frequently Asked Questions
  items:
    - question: What makes the database truly immutable?
      answer: Our database uses blockchain technology with cryptographic hashing. Once data is written, it cannot be altered or deleted without leaving a permanent record of the change, ensuring complete data integrity.
    - question: How does it integrate with existing systems?
      answer: We provide comprehensive REST APIs, SDKs for major programming languages, and webhook support for real-time notifications. Our team also offers integration support to ensure smooth deployment.
    - question: What happens if a node goes down?
      answer: Our distributed architecture ensures that data remains available even if multiple nodes fail. Data is replicated across the network, providing high availability and fault tolerance.
    - question: Is my data encrypted?
      answer: Yes, all data is encrypted both in transit (using TLS) and at rest (using AES-256 encryption). Additionally, we use cryptographic hashing to ensure data integrity.
    - question: Can I export my data?
      answer: Absolutely. You maintain full ownership of your data and can export it at any time through our API or web interface in various formats including JSON, CSV, and XML.

